## Channel Architecture — Plan Panel vs Chat Feed

### Chat Feed (`onUpdate`) — Shared/Single Channel

Each `onUpdate` call goes to the tool API's `execute` callback (defined by `pi.registerTool({... execute(toolCallId, params, signal, onUpdate, ctx) })`).

In `delegate-tool.ts`, `onUpdate` is **wrapped** but not fanned out:
```ts
const wrappedOnUpdate = (update: any) => {
    if (update.details?.tool) { /* count metrics */ }
    onUpdate?.(update);  // ← passes through to the SAME single channel
};
```

The tool API stores a **single `result` object** per tool call. Each `onUpdate` call **replaces** `result.content[0].text`. The `renderResult` function reads `result?.content?.[0]?.text` at render time — this is **always the last onUpdate's text**.

Additionally, `renderResult` in `delegate-tool.ts` has its **own 80ms interval** that calls `context.invalidate()` to trigger re-renders:
```ts
if (isPartial && !state.interval) {
    state.interval = setInterval(() => {
        getSpinnerIndex(); // tick shared spinner
        context.invalidate();
    }, 80);
}
```

This means the chat feed has **TWO timers fighting** at the same 80ms frequency but unsynchronized:
1. **Render timer** in subagent-runner.ts — calls `onUpdate` with formatted feed text
2. **Invalidate timer** in delegate-tool's `renderResult` — triggers re-render of the LATEST `state.lastFeedText`

### Plan Panel (`updatePlanStepDetail`) — Dedicated Channel

`updatePlanStepDetail` writes directly to the TUI widget system:
```ts
export function updatePlanStepDetail(detail: string | string[]): void {
    if (!planState) return;
    const idx = planState.steps.findIndex((s) => s.active);
    if (idx >= 0) {
        if (Array.isArray(detail)) {
            planState.steps[idx].detailLines = detail.length > 0 ? detail : undefined;
            planState.steps[idx].detail = undefined;
        } else {
            planState.steps[idx].detail = detail || undefined;
            planState.steps[idx].detailLines = undefined;
        }
        _renderWidget();  // ← calls _setWidget(WIDGET_KEY, lines) — TUI API
    }
}
```

`_renderWidget` → `_setWidget(WIDGET_KEY, lines)` writes to the TUI widget system. This is a completely separate API from `onUpdate`. No competition.

### Wiring Summary

```
subagent-runner.ts
├── onUpdate() ──────────────────→ delegate-tool.ts wrappedOnUpdate ──→ tool API's onUpdate ──→ chat feed (SINGLE CHANNEL)
│                                                                                                      ↑
│   8 competing call sites:                                                                        renderResult reads
│   ├─ text_delta (streaming:true)                                                             state.lastFeedText
│   ├─ message_end (assistant)
│   ├─ message_end (lint-guard)
│   ├─ tool_execution_start
│   ├─ tool_execution_update
│   ├─ tool_execution_end
│   ├─ renderTimer (80ms) ←─── COMPETES WITH ALL ABOVE
│   └─ error handler
│
└── updatePlanStepDetail() ──→ plan-panel.ts _renderWidget() ──→ _setWidget(WIDGET_KEY) ──→ TUI Widget (DEDICATED CHANNEL)
    Only 3 call sites:
    ├─ tool_execution_start
    ├─ tool_execution_update
    └─ tool_execution_end
```

