        // Assert rendered output matches recorded
        if (frame.feedRender) {
            const rendered = renderActivityFeed("scout", feed);
            expect(stripAnsi(rendered)).toContain(frame.feedRender);
        }
    }

    // Final state assertions
    expect(feed.currentStep).toBe(feed.steps.length);
    expect(feed.steps.every(s => s.completed)).toBe(true);
});
```

### Why this beats any terminal emulator

| Approach | Determinism | Tests real logic | Catches regressions | Setup cost |
|----------|-------------|-----------------|-------------------|------------|
| Terminal emulator | ❌ Flaky timing | ❌ Tests terminal, not logic | ⚠️ Indirect | High |
| **Timeline replay** | ✅ Same input = same output | ✅ Tests feed state machine + rendering | ✅ Output change = test fail | **Zero** — you already have the files |
| Pure function unit tests | ✅ | ✅ Partial | ✅ | Medium |

### The full testing strategy

```
RECORD                          TEST
──────                          ────
Run orchestrator             timeline-replay.test.ts
  → timeline.json              → replay events through
  → every frame captured          feed state machine
                                → assert output matches
