Here's what `reportFinding()` would look like:

### The tool

```typescript
session.registerTool("reportFinding", {
    description: "Report an important finding discovered during execution. Call this when you find something noteworthy.",
    parameters: Type.Object({
        finding: Type.String({ description: "What you discovered" }),
    }),
    execute: async (_toolCallId, params) => {
        if (feed.currentStep >= 0 && feed.currentStep < feed.steps.length) {
            const step = feed.steps[feed.currentStep];
            const newSubstep = {
                label: params.finding,
                completed: true,
                isReport: true,
                startTime: Date.now(),
                endTime: Date.now(),
            };
            const newSubsteps = [...step.substeps, newSubstep];
            const newSteps = feed.steps.map((s, i) =>
                i === feed.currentStep ? { ...s, substeps: newSubsteps } : s
            );
            feed = { ...feed, steps: newSteps };
            // Emit render
            const text = renderActivityFeed(specialist.name, feed);
            onUpdate?.({ content: [{ type: "text", text }], details: { status: "running" } });
            return { content: [{ type: "text", text: `Reported: ${params.finding}` }], details: {} };
        }
        return { content: [{ type: "text", text: "No active step to report under" }], details: {} };
    },
});
```

### Subagent sees

```
Finding something important?
  → call reportFinding("JWT secret is hardcoded in config.ts")
  → appears in feed as:
    ✓ Report: JWT secret is hardcoded in config.ts
```

